<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-097-680  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 097 680.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Feb 20 1989 n302 p103(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Industry welcomes $2.2B aid to NSF. (Corporate Closeup) (NationalScience Foundation) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pang, Albert.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The National Science Foundation (NSF) receives a pledge fromPresident Bush of $2.2 billion for basic research.andP;  Computer userswho rely on NSF for support in nationwide networking applaud thispledge.andP;  NSF has a national computer network, called NSF Net,which links over 200 college campuses and large corporations.andP;  Thenetwork permits users to share research data and gain access tosupercomputers installed at NSF and the US Department of Defense.andO;More than 10,000 users exchange electronic mail messages everyday.andP;  A transcontinental transmission on NSF Net takes about 200milliseconds.andP;  NSF Net brings the computer efficiency found inmainframe and supercomputer environments to the workstation andmicrocomputer areas.andP;  The national government could encourage thestandardization of protocols and could encourage the developmentof a more sophisticated security system to prevent spreading ofviruses.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. National Science FoundationResearch and DevelopmentNSFNET (Computer network)Electronic Mail SystemsNational Government.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>